Interface Time

All Known Subinterfaces:
Timer
All Known Implementing Classes:
ExactTimer, MilliTime, NanoTime, SamplingTimer, SteppingTimer
public interface Time

A time source.

The time() method provide a measure of elapsed time, for some arbitrary notion of time and since some arbitrary origin.

More formally, the only contract on this method is that on any call, it returns values that are not smaller than any value returned by a previous call.
